WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.653
Start in Operations and look down the sidebar.

p02
00:00:03.333 --> 00:00:05.639
The whole module is laid out in three groups.

p03
00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:07.430
Maintenance sits at the top, then Incident Reports, then the Scheduler pages.

p04
00:00:07.857 --> 00:00:10.730
We are in Maintenance, where five entries stack together.

p05
00:00:11.596 --> 00:00:14.512
The first is Issues, the work-order list you already know.

p06
00:00:15.106 --> 00:00:18.341
The four below it are the planned side of upkeep,

p07
00:00:18.889 --> 00:00:21.244
the routines and gear and parts that sit behind every ticket.

p08
00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:27.079
That set is today's tour.

p09
00:00:27.567 --> 00:00:28.937
Click Maintenance Schedule.

p10
00:00:29.634 --> 00:00:31.508
This is the planned side of upkeep.

p11
00:00:31.980 --> 00:00:37.769
Forty two recurring tasks live on this calendar, six due this week and two already overdue.

p12
00:00:38.442 --> 00:00:40.215
Each row is a job that repeats:

p13
00:00:40.553 --> 00:00:42.339
lubricate the conveyor chain weekly, inspect the chemical pumps once a month.

p14
00:00:42.648 --> 00:00:44.734
The column a manager reads first is Next Due,

p15
00:00:45.390 --> 00:00:51.840
because it names the service that is coming before anything breaks.

p16
00:00:52.313 --> 00:00:54.019
Now Equipment Registry.

p17
00:00:54.401 --> 00:00:56.935
Every machine a work order points back to.

p18
00:00:57.168 --> 00:00:59.125
This tenant carries four assets:

p19
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:00.304
a blower system, a chemical pump array, the main tunnel conveyor, and a point of sale terminal.

p20
00:01:00.518 --> 00:01:04.943
Three are operational and one sits in repair.

p21
00:01:05.204 --> 00:01:07.894
When a caller says the air dryer is down,

p22
00:01:08.158 --> 00:01:16.080
this page names the exact unit, places it at its site, and shows whether it is already flagged.

p23
00:01:16.589 --> 00:01:17.286
Open Checklists.

p24
00:01:17.286 --> 00:01:23.869
These are the fixed steps a tech follows so nothing gets skipped on a busy day.

p25
00:01:23.869 --> 00:01:28.959
Daily opening and closing walks, a weekly safety inspection, a monthly deep clean.

p26
00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:32.708
The completion column shows how faithfully each one gets done,

p27
00:01:32.708 --> 00:01:36.177
and the average sits at ninety four percent.

p28
00:01:36.177 --> 00:01:36.874
One caution.

p29
00:01:36.874 --> 00:01:41.005
This is not the Lube Checklists page over in Hardware settings.

p30
00:01:41.005 --> 00:01:42.399
Different place, different job.

p31
00:01:42.955 --> 00:01:45.074
Last one. Parts and Supplies.

p32
00:01:45.753 --> 00:01:47.532
The stock a repair pulls from.

p33
00:01:48.046 --> 00:01:48.897
Drive belts, pump seal kits, dryer filters, a spare power supply.

p34
00:01:49.146 --> 00:01:52.810
A hundred forty two parts, about eighteen thousand dollars sitting on the shelf.

p35
00:01:53.259 --> 00:01:57.460
Read quantity on hand against the reorder point

p36
00:01:57.826 --> 00:02:03.663
and you can answer a do we have it call in seconds.

p37
00:02:04.005 --> 00:02:07.177
And keep it straight from Chemicals and Supplies over in Inventory;

p38
00:02:07.454 --> 00:02:12.351
that page is wash chemistry and retail goods, this one is upkeep.

p39
00:02:12.351 --> 00:02:13.289
So, the map.

p40
00:02:14.017 --> 00:02:17.719
Four live pages under Maintenance, right beside Issues.

p41
00:02:18.487 --> 00:02:20.483
A recurring job lands on the Schedule, and Next Due says when.

p42
00:02:20.772 --> 00:02:22.348
A question about a machine goes to the Registry.

p43
00:02:23.029 --> 00:02:25.466
The steps a tech follows are the Checklists.

p44
00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:28.712
The parts a repair burns through are Parts and Supplies.

p45
00:02:29.243 --> 00:02:32.578
One habit before you go.

p46
00:02:33.518 --> 00:02:34.979
Reach these pages from the sidebar inside Operations,

p47
00:02:35.584 --> 00:02:42.446
because typing an address straight into the browser still fails.

p48
00:02:43.094 --> 00:02:44.880
The sidebar is the front door.

